This paper is about improving the speed and energy efficiency of training deep neural networks using mixed precision training. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, given that the paper focuses on improving the training process for deep neural networks, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CV and cs.NE.
